				Being the greedy Wizard that I am, I buy all the spells I can, even the &quot;worthless&quot; ones. My favorite &quot;worthless&quot; spell so far is &quot;Eye of Zomm&quot;. It is great for zipping along and spying out distant monsters or enemy camps, and, more importantly, you can choose your target carefully, from very long range. It's also great for scaring the crap out of newbies, so be careful not to fall out of your chair as you watch them scatter to the four corners.<BR>
<BR>
One important tactic to remember as a wizard- how to over come spell resistance. Casting that &quot;Shock of Ice&quot; spell is just dandy, but on some monsters it soon does less and less damage, as they seem to build up some kind of &quot;resistance&quot; to it. Or maybe they are already popsicles, and extra freezing just isn't doing the trick. Whatever the case, alternate in with the old tried and true &quot;Shock of Fire&quot; or even an extravagant &quot;Fire Bolt&quot; and thaw them back out again! Then you can nail them again with the more manna efficient &quot;Shock of Ice&quot;.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
